{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_135","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"nl -ba docs/experiment_orchestration_notes/FW-M15-002_rationale.md | sed -n '1,220p'\"","aggregated_output":"     1\t# FW-M15-002 Rationale\n     2\t\n     3\t## Design Choices\n     4\t\n     5\tThis ticket adds one library-owned planner module,\n     6\t`flywire_wave.experiment_suite_planning`, instead of spreading Milestone 15\n     7\tsuite parsing across later runners, reporting code, or ad hoc scripts.\n     8\t\n     9\tThe planner deliberately composes with earlier milestone layers:\n    10\t\n    11\t- it resolves one reusable base `simulation_plan.v1`\n    12\t- it reuses the embedded readout-analysis pairing surface from that plan\n    13\t- it emits suite cells, work items, and planned artifact references through\n    14\t  `experiment_suite.v1`\n    15\t- it does not replace the Milestone 9 through Milestone 14 bundle contracts\n    16\t\n    17\tThe normalized suite surface therefore stays at the orchestration layer:\n    18\t\n    19\t- dimensions declare sweep intent plus deterministic overrides or snapshots\n    20\t- seed policy declares how simulator seeds are reused across suite cells\n    21\t- ablation declarations stay explicit and lineage-tracked\n    22\t- stage targets and output roots are deterministic before execution starts\n    23\t\n    24\tI also added one new config path default,\n    25\t`paths.processed_experiment_suites_dir`, so the suite planner has a stable\n    26\tlocal root without forcing each caller to invent its own directory convention.\n    27\t\n    28\t## Why The Planner Stops At Planned Cells Instead Of Full Derived Bundles\n    29\t\n    30\tMilestone 15 still has later tickets for execution, ablation realization, and\n    31\tsuite packaging. This planner therefore normalizes intent and deterministic\n    32\tlineage now, but it does not yet:\n    33\t\n    34\t- materialize per-cell experiment manifests on disk\n    35\t- run simulation, analysis, validation, or dashboard stages\n    36\t- realize the scientific transforms behind each ablation family\n    37\t- publish one finalized suite bundle layout with persisted metadata\n    38\t\n    39\tThat split is intentional. The planner now gives later workflow code one\n    40\tstable, typed surface to consume instead of rediscovering sweep expansion,\n    41\tseed reuse, and ablation attachment rules in multiple places.\n    42\t\n    43\t## Testing Strategy\n    44\t\n    45\tThe regression coverage for this ticket focuses on normalization behavior and\n    46\tfailure clarity:\n    47\t\n    48\t- deterministic resolution of a representative suite manifest into stable base,\n    49\t  seed, ablation, and seeded-ablation cells\n    50\t- config-versus-manifest precedence for stage targets, output roots, and seed\n    51\t  defaults\n    52\t- embedded experiment-manifest `suite` extensions as an alternative input path\n    53\t- explicit failure handling for unknown dimension IDs, linked-axis length\n    54\t  mismatches, unsupported ablation variants, contradictory perturbation-seed\n    55\t  rules, and missing subset prerequisites\n    56\t\n    57\tThe suite-planning tests intentionally reuse the existing simulation fixture\n    58\thelpers so the new planner is exercised on the same manifest/config ecosystem\n    59\tas the earlier milestone planners.\n    60\t\n    61\t## Simplifications\n    62\t\n    63\tThe first version intentionally keeps several boundaries conservative:\n    64\t\n    65\t- ablation declarations use a small, explicit variant-id set per family\n    66\t- dimension values may carry parameter snapshots or override patches even when\n    67\t  later execution still has to interpret those patches\n    68\t- suite-level output references are planned metadata targets, not yet persisted\n    69\t  bundle files\n    70\t- wave-dependent dimensions and ablations fail early when the base manifest has\n    71\t  no surface-wave arm instead of pretending those requests are meaningful\n    72\t\n    73\tThese choices bias toward explicitness and clear failure over premature\n    74\tgeneralization.\n    75\t\n    76\t## Future Expansion Points\n    77\t\n    78\tThe next Milestone 15 tickets can build directly on this normalized surface:\n    79\t\n    80\t- `FW-M15-003` can execute the emitted suite cells and work items in stable\n    81\t  order\n    82\t- `FW-M15-004` can replace planning-only ablation declarations with realized\n    83\t  transforms\n    84\t- `FW-M15-005` can persist the planned artifact roots as one suite-owned index\n    85\t- `FW-M15-006` and `FW-M15-007` can aggregate and report from the same\n    86\t  deterministic lineage and pairing surface\n    87\t\n    88\tIf later work needs different sweep semantics, seed semantics, or stage-role\n    89\tmeanings, that should be a new planner version rather than a silent behavioral\n    90\tchange.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
